  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIC Bank Limited</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is IFCs first project with NIC Bank and is intended to provide long term funding that will strengthen the Banks capital base, diversify its funding sources and support the expansion of term lending for the SME sector. IFCs investment will ultimately support the Banks medium term growth strategy.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">i. Improve access to finance for SMEs: The Project will allow NIC to grow its SME portfolio and provide this crucial segment of the economy with access to longer term funding, thereby enabling SME&apos;&apos;s to undertake investment projects with more appropriate financing structures. ii.	IFC&apos;&apos;s subordinated loan will strengthen the capital base of the Bank. This will ensure that NIC complies with new regulatory capital requirements that are aimed at improving the overall risk profile of the banking sector iii.	Enhancing regional competition and service.  The project will contribute to the success of the East African economic community by supporting a strong local bank with a growing regional footprint.</narrative>
  </description>
